  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Sales Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Who You Are</strong><br /></p><ul><li><p>Min 3 years in a customer-facing technical role (Sales Engineering, Field Apps, Integration, Solutions Engineering).<br /></p></li><li><p>Strong hands-on understanding of RF propagation, antennas, interference mitigation, and wireless networking.<br /></p></li><li><p>Experience integrating radios into UAV/autonomy platforms (command-and-control, telemetry, high-throughput data links).<br /></p></li><li><p>Skilled communicator who thrives in field environments solving real-world engineering challenges.<br /></p></li><li><p>Motivated by ownership and high accountability — your work directly influences customer success and program outcomes.<br /></p></li></ul><p><strong>Nice to Have</strong><br /></p><ul><li><p>Familiarity with mesh networking concepts (mobile MANET routing, distributed networks).<br /></p></li><li><p>TCP/IP configuration and troubleshooting experience.<br /></p></li><li><p>Background supporting DoD programs, defense primes, or DIU prototypes.<br /></p></li><li><p>Experience with autonomy OEMs (industrial drones, logistics AMRs, maritime robotics).<br /></p></li></ul><p><strong>Additional Details</strong><br /></p><ul><li><p>Travel: Up to 50%</p></li></ul>",
